The paper discusses the use of algorithms for buried threat detection using ground penetrating radar, which involves computer vision and image processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with the performance evaluation of different algorithms, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for optimization, which could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
